===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|palais}}, which comes from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|palātium}}, from {{m|la|Palātium}}, in reference to the [[Palatine]] Hill, one of the seven hills of Rome, where the aristocracy of the Roman [[republic|Republic]]—and later, Roman emperors—built large, splendid residences. The name is ultimately either from {{etyl|ett|en}}, the same source as {{m|la|Pales||{{w|Pales}}, the Italic goddess of shepherds, flocks and livestock}}, or Latin {{m|la|palus||stake; enclosure}}.

